dia:content height="1333" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-05/19863250-d204-11ec-bd2d-37f4ef930698" width="2000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Billy Steele/Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[With upgrades to design, sound quality and active noise cancellation, the WH-1000XM5 keeps its place above the competition. These headphones are super comfortable as well, and 30-hour battery life is more than adequate. The M5 makes it clear that Sony won’t be dethroned anytime soon.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Sony WH-1000XM5 review]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Judge tosses Republican lawsuit against Google over Gmail spam filters]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>去年，共和党全国委员会 (RNC) 对谷歌<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/the-republican-national-committee-sues-google-over-gmail-spam-filters-173722812.html">提起诉讼，</a>指控其 Gmail 垃圾邮件过滤器存在政治偏见。据<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.washingtonpost.com/technology/2023/08/24/rnc-google-lawsuit-dismissed-spam-filter/"><em>《华盛顿邮报》</em></a>报道，现在，一名联邦法官驳回了该诉讼，指出谷歌受到美国法律第 230 条的有效保护，并且共和党全国委员会没有通过过滤竞选电子邮件来“充分证明谷歌的恶意行为” 。</p><p>根据诉讼，谷歌故意将“ <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.axios.com/2022/10/22/rnc-lawsuit-google-spam-filter-blocks-email">数百万</a>”的共和党全国委员会电子邮件标记为垃圾邮件，因此该组织寻求赔偿“据称因此损失的捐款”。作为证据，它引用了一项研究发现，Gmail 比雅虎和其他邮件系统更有可能将共和党电子邮件标记为垃圾邮件。 （该研究的一位作者<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/2022/05/25/republicans-seized-study-proof-googles-bias-its-authors-say-it-being-misrepresented/">去年告诉《<em>华盛顿邮报》</em></a> ，其研究结果是经过精心挑选的。）</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>美国地方法院法官丹尼尔·卡拉布雷塔称该诉讼为“结案”，他表示共和党全国委员会“未能合理地声称”谷歌的垃圾邮件过滤是恶意进行的。谷歌表示，由于用户投诉，相关电子邮件很可能被标记为垃圾邮件，并指出 RNC 域身份验证问题和频繁的邮件发送是其他潜在问题。</p><p>法院还裁定，根据《 <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2019-09-11-did-ai-kill-off-spam-and-we-just-didn-t-notice.html">反垃圾邮件法》</a> ，RNC 电子邮件可能被视为“令人反感”，而 Google 对其进行标记的事实受到第 230 条的保护，该条规定在线平台免受基于第三方的民事责任内容。尽管如此，法官表示共和党人仍然可以修改诉讼，以更好地证明谷歌缺乏诚意。</p><p>有趣的是，在去年的美国中期选举期间，谷歌制造了一个<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-political-campaign-emails-spam-fec-approval-183735778.html">漏洞</a>，允许政治竞选活动躲避 Gmail 垃圾邮件过滤器。然而， <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.theverge.com/2022/10/13/23403259/google-gmail-republicans-gop-spam-filtering-program-midterms">据报道，</a>共和党全国委员会并没有利用该计划。由于公众的反馈<a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.fec.gov/files/legal/aos/2022-14/202214C_01.pdf">大多是负面的</a>，谷歌随后结束了该实验。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/judge-tosses-republican-lawsuit-against-google-over-gmail-spam-filters-075622648.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/judge-tosses-republican-lawsuit-against-google-over-gmail-spam-filters-075622648.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 35f2da9f-ae84-4f14-8194-d908d4d53377</guid><dc:creator>史蒂夫·登特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Mon, 28 Aug 2023 07:56:22 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1693209382</ingested><modified> 2023-08-28T07:56:26+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Company Legal & Law Matters]]></category><category><![CDATA[Business]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Steve Dent]]></category><media:content height="3005" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/dd315490-4572-11ee-beeb-1d00bb0d2e5c" width="4517"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[